The paper deals with the problem of finding a set of nodes in a social network that can maximize the spread of influence. This problem is a classic topic in social network analysis and falls under the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Social Computing (cs.SOC). The paper also presents algorithms for trees, paths, cycles, and complete graphs, which are all topics in the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper uses dynamic programming and optimization techniques, which are common in the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
